Michael Douglas, 77, penned a poignant message to his famous dad, Kirk Douglas, as he celebrated Father’s Day without him.The Fatal Attraction actor shared a childhood photograph of himself and Kirk.Kirk can be seen relaxing on a sofa as a young Michael looks over his shoulder at the magazine they are reading.In a sweet caption, Michael penned in view of his one million followers: “You will always be an inspiration. I miss you Dad!” Kirk, who was famed for his roles in Spartacus and Paths Of Glory, died in 2020 aged 103.